  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants in San Sebastian that won't burn a hole in your pocket?",
  "response": "San Sebastian (Donostia) is renowned for its incredible culinary scene, especially its pintxos bars and Michelin-starred restaurants. While it\u2019s easy to spend a lot on dining here, there are plenty of affordable and delicious options that won\u2019t break the bank. Here are some of the best budget-friendly restaurants and pintxos bars in San Sebastian:\n\n### **Pintxos Bars**\n1. **Bar Borda Berri**  \n   - Known for its creative and high-quality pintxos, this spot is a favorite among locals and visitors alike. Try the risotto or braised beef cheeks.  \n   - Address: Ferm\u00edn Calbet\u00f3n Kalea, 12.\n\n2. **La Cuchara de San Telmo**  \n   - Though slightly more upscale than other pintxos bars, this spot offers generous portions of gourmet pintxos at reasonable prices. The foie gras and slow-cooked pork are must-tries.  \n   - Address: Santa Korda Kalea, 4.\n\n3. **Bar Zeruko**  \n   - A modern pintxos bar with inventive and artistic dishes. Their \"smoking pintxo\" is famous and a must-tSarah Hill uses art as her way to combat the struggles in her life. Through creativity, critical thinking, and faith she is able to grow and inspire others to do the same. Sarah\u2019s mission with this collection is to empower and encourage others to embrace the storm of their season in both good times and bad. We are unique, we are worthy, and we are loved\u2026 no matter what. Each canvas of art has a story that dives into pieces of the struggles and triumphs that Sarah has encountered thus far and the lessons she has learned from the experiences. She wants to share her journey and to remind you that you are not alone and that you are capable of doing the impossible. Not only will each piece of artwork be a stunning addition to any space, it will also serve as a positive reminder in both good times and bad. Find the piece that speaks to you and that will encourage you on your own beautiful journey.\n\nSarah believes that the tough times are not meant to break us, but grow us into the person we are meant to be. In order to grow we need to embrace our situation for what it is and find the beauty in the storm. It\u2019s easy to fight against our struggles and curse the brokenness, but life becomes more vibrant when we can have the mindset to learn and grow from the challenges that face us. Every negative situation serves a purpose and will one day develop us into the person we are meant to become. Find the beauty and let it strengthens you and the ones around you. You\u2019ll be amazed at the storms that you will be able to survive through with this mindset.\n\n\nAreas of Work: Creativity, Water, Paint, Mixed Media Canvas | Website | Facebook",
  "temperature": 1.0,
